Research on Cybersecurity Tools 
Introduction 
Cybersecurity tools help organizations protect their networks, systems, and data from cyber threats. They are used to identify vulnerabilities, monitor network traffic, detect attacks, and secure sensitive information. This report discusses three widely used cybersecurity tools: Wireshark, Nmap, and Metasploit Framework. 
  
1. Wireshark 
Overview 
Wireshark is a free and open-source network protocol analyzer used to capture and inspect network traffic in real time. It helps security professionals understand how data flows across a network and identify suspicious or malicious activities. 
Features 
•	Captures live network packets. 
•	Supports hundreds of network protocols. 
•	Filters traffic for detailed analysis. 
•	Provides graphical and statistical reports. 
•	Helps troubleshoot network issues. 
Advantages 
•	Free and open source. • 	User-friendly interface. 
•	Powerful packet analysis capabilities. 
•	Widely used by network administrators and security analysts. 
Limitations 
•	Requires networking knowledge. 
•	Cannot prevent attacks; it only analyzes network traffic. 
Common Uses 
•	Network troubleshooting. 
•	Malware traffic analysis. 
•	Security investigations. 
•	Performance monitoring. 
  
2. Nmap (Network Mapper) 
Overview 
Nmap is one of the most popular network scanning tools used to discover devices, identify open ports, detect operating systems, and find running services on a network. It is widely used by penetration testers and system administrators. 
Features 
•	Host discovery. 

•	Port scanning. 
•	Operating system detection. 
•	Service version detection. 
•	Network security auditing. 
Advantages 
•	Fast and reliable. 
•	Supports multiple scanning techniques. 
•	Free and open source. 
•	Helps identify security weaknesses. 
Limitations 
•	May be detected by firewalls or intrusion detection systems. 
•	Incorrect usage may generate unnecessary network traffic. 
Common Uses 
•	Network inventory. 
•	Vulnerability assessment. 
•	Security auditing. 
•	Penetration testing. 
  
3. Metasploit Framework 
Overview 
Metasploit Framework is a powerful penetration testing tool used to identify, verify, and exploit security vulnerabilities in computer systems. It allows security professionals to test the effectiveness of their security controls in a controlled environment. 
Features 
•	Large collection of exploit modules. 
•	Payload generation. 
•	Vulnerability validation. 
•	Post-exploitation modules. 
•	Integration with vulnerability scanners. 
Advantages 
•	Widely accepted penetration testing framework. 
•	Regularly updated with new exploits. 
•	Supports automation. 
•	Excellent for security research and training. 
Limitations 
•	Requires technical expertise. 
•	Should only be used with proper authorization. 
•	Misuse can violate laws and organizational policies. 
Common Uses 
•	Ethical hacking. 
•	Penetration testing. 
•	Security research. 
•	Vulnerability verification. 
  
