Conclusion 
Wireshark, Nmap, and Metasploit Framework are essential cybersecurity tools used for different security tasks. Wireshark analyzes network traffic, Nmap discovers devices and scans networks, while Metasploit helps security professionals test and validate vulnerabilities. Together, these tools improve an organization's ability to detect security issues, assess risks, and strengthen overall cybersecurity defenses. Proper training and authorized use are essential to maximize their effectiveness and ensure ethical cybersecurity practices
